WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.637 --> 00:00:14.179
Need some help over here!

2
00:00:14.180 --> 00:00:15.764
- Who called in SWAT?
- Just a precaution.

3
00:00:15.765 --> 00:00:17.307
They still haven't
found the shooter yet.

4
00:00:17.308 --> 00:00:19.268
They need to stay out
there. not in here.

5
00:00:19.269 --> 00:00:21.645
Officer down. You
know the drill.

6
00:00:21.646 --> 00:00:23.814
- 16 gauge in the right AC.
- Definitely needs an airway.

7
00:00:23.815 --> 00:00:25.149
Can you handle that bleeding?

8
00:00:25.150 --> 00:00:26.817
Need a sponge
stick for the back.

9
00:00:26.818 --> 00:00:28.736
Dana. 100 of ketamine and
get some 4x4s on a kelly.

10
00:00:28.737 --> 00:00:30.320
You guys are doing a
great job. Keep it up.

11
00:00:30.321 --> 00:00:33.157
Hang in there. Richie.
You're in good hands.

12
00:00:33.158 --> 00:00:35.826
You're gonna be okay. man.
- Hey. guys.

13
00:00:35.827 --> 00:00:37.286
Back it up. We're
trying to work here.

14
00:00:37.287 --> 00:00:39.121
Come on. Both of youse. go.

15
00:00:39.122 --> 00:00:42.166
And chest tube
output is minimal.

16
00:00:42.167 --> 00:00:44.877
Good for cardiothoracic ICU.
- Nice. Okay.

17
00:00:44.878 --> 00:00:46.545
As soon as transpo
can lend us a hand.

18
00:00:46.546 --> 00:00:48.464
What's up with the SWAT team?

19
00:00:48.465 --> 00:00:49.965
Maybe they think the
shooter's coming here.

20
00:00:49.966 --> 00:00:51.216
- Shit. is that true?
- What?

21
00:00:51.217 --> 00:00:52.718
My kid's in the break room.

22
00:00:52.719 --> 00:00:54.344
They think the shooter's
heading this way?

23
00:00:54.345 --> 00:00:56.847
Anything is possible.

24
00:00:56.848 --> 00:00:59.516
Don't spread rumors.

25
00:00:59.517 --> 00:01:01.143
I'm taking this one to the OR.

26
00:01:06.191 --> 00:01:07.483
How are you doing?

27
00:01:07.484 --> 00:01:09.777
Yeah. I'm good. You?

28
00:01:09.778 --> 00:01:11.320
I'm good.

29
00:01:11.321 --> 00:01:12.863
How much blood are we getting?
- I don't know.

30
00:01:12.864 --> 00:01:14.239
I hope it's enough.

31
00:01:14.240 --> 00:01:15.491
We're supposed to stop here

32
00:01:15.492 --> 00:01:17.826
and stay between
10:00 and 2:00.

33
00:01:17.827 --> 00:01:20.204
- Where's 12?
- I think the pilot's 12.

34
00:01:20.205 --> 00:01:24.042
I think we just stay back. and
they bring the blood to us.

35
00:01:25.585 --> 00:01:27.253
I think.

36
00:01:29.589 --> 00:01:30.547
- Here.
- Thank you.

37
00:01:30.548 --> 00:01:31.966
Yep.

38
00:01:36.054 --> 00:01:37.471
Do we take these
to our supply room

39
00:01:37.472 --> 00:01:39.223
in Behavioral Health?
- Trauma rooms first.

40
00:01:39.224 --> 00:01:41.225
Then we'll make our way out
to the patients in the hub.

41
00:01:41.226 --> 00:01:43.352
- That the O-neg delivery?
- Yeah. straight from the roof.

42
00:01:43.353 --> 00:01:45.062
Jesse. hang a unit.
then right up to the OR.

43
00:01:45.063 --> 00:01:46.897
Who else needs blood?

44
00:01:46.898 --> 00:01:48.732
Everybody.

45
00:01:48.733 --> 00:01:50.359
Leave us four units.
four next door.

46
00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:52.111
and then check in
with Robby and Abbot.

47
00:01:52.112 --> 00:01:54.613
Okay. I've got next door.

48
00:01:54.614 --> 00:01:56.198
- Blood's here.
- All right.

49
00:01:56.199 --> 00:01:57.533
Squeeze one in as
fast as you can.

50
00:01:57.534 --> 00:01:59.576
Bag for me.

51
00:01:59.577 --> 00:02:02.246
- You guys need blood?
- No. not just yet.

52
00:02:02.247 --> 00:02:03.747
Leave it with Dana.

53
00:02:03.748 --> 00:02:05.415
Hey. Whitaker. How you doing?

54
00:02:05.416 --> 00:02:06.416
Yeah. fine.

55
00:02:06.417 --> 00:02:07.751
Ask for help if you need it.

56
00:02:07.752 --> 00:02:10.420
I can't see the
cords. Let's bag him.

57
00:02:10.421 --> 00:02:11.922
Sorry. I'm used
to the GlideScope.

58
00:02:11.923 --> 00:02:13.382
Spoiled by technology.

59
00:02:13.383 --> 00:02:14.800
Dana. you got a
bougie back there?

60
00:02:14.801 --> 00:02:17.136
Completely out.
Used them all up.

61
00:02:17.137 --> 00:02:20.639
- Is he awake?
- He was. Now he's sedated.

62
00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:22.975
- Should be intubated by now.
- Yeah. what's his pulse ox?

63
00:02:22.976 --> 00:02:24.434
All right. except
for his partner.

64
00:02:24.435 --> 00:02:26.270
all of you into BH-2 now.

65
00:02:26.271 --> 00:02:27.771
You can watch from the window.

66
00:02:27.772 --> 00:02:29.773
but you need to zip it. capisce?

67
00:02:29.774 --> 00:02:31.441
Oh. God. Bridget. thank God.

68
00:02:31.442 --> 00:02:32.693
Night shift to the rescue.

69
00:02:32.694 --> 00:02:33.902
What the hell
happened to your eye?

70
00:02:33.903 --> 00:02:35.404
Just another happy customer.

71
00:02:35.405 --> 00:02:37.239
Looks a lot worse than it is.
- Yeah. right.

72
00:02:37.240 --> 00:02:39.741
I tried to get here sooner.
but it is gridlocked out there.

73
00:02:39.742 --> 00:02:41.118
It's not much better in here.

74
00:02:41.119 --> 00:02:43.036
Did you hear anything
about the shooter?

75
00:02:43.037 --> 00:02:45.622
They may have slipped away in
the crowd with all this chaos.

76
00:02:45.623 --> 00:02:48.167
Hey. where do you need me?
- North is yellow.

77
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:49.918
Keep an eye on the new kids.
- Got it.

78
00:02:49.919 --> 00:02:50.961
You holler if you're in trouble.

79
00:02:50.962 --> 00:02:53.338
Yes. ma'am.

80
00:02:53.339 --> 00:02:55.799
Jamie. what do you need?

81
00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:57.301
IVs on everyone.

82
00:02:57.302 --> 00:03:00.220
- Hi. I'm Dr. King.
- Buster Pirelli.

83
00:03:00.221 --> 00:03:03.140
I take it you're a
children's entertainer.

84
00:03:03.141 --> 00:03:04.808
Impressive observational skills.

85
00:03:04.809 --> 00:03:06.393
Well. no active bleeding.

86
00:03:06.394 --> 00:03:08.812
Can you tell me your pain
on a scale of 1 to 10?

87
00:03:08.813 --> 00:03:10.147
At least a 3.

88
00:03:10.148 --> 00:03:11.815
And can you wiggle your fingers?

89
00:03:11.816 --> 00:03:14.109
Uh-huh.

90
00:03:14.110 --> 00:03:15.485
The... the other hand.

91
00:03:15.486 --> 00:03:17.613
Oh.

92
00:03:17.614 --> 00:03:19.364
Well. it doesn't seem like
you have a broken bone.

93
00:03:19.365 --> 00:03:21.325
but we're gonna put you
on some IV antibiotics

94
00:03:21.326 --> 00:03:22.826
and some pain meds.

95
00:03:22.827 --> 00:03:23.953
Got it.

96
00:03:25.622 --> 00:03:27.497
You. uh. see who shot you?

97
00:03:27.498 --> 00:03:31.418
No. I'm not even sure which
direction the bullet came from.

98
00:03:31.419 --> 00:03:34.922
Hey. am I going to lose
any dexterity? Like...

99
00:03:34.923 --> 00:03:37.174
It's too soon to tell.
but probably not.

100
00:03:37.175 --> 00:03:39.343
I make balloon
animals for a living.

101
00:03:39.344 --> 00:03:41.470
Two birthday parties booked
every Saturday. Sunday

102
00:03:41.471 --> 00:03:43.096
for the next year. so...

103
00:03:43.097 --> 00:03:45.599
Wow. you must really love kids.

104
00:03:45.600 --> 00:03:47.142
Not really.

105
00:03:47.143 --> 00:03:48.644
Okay. you're gonna feel
a little pinprick here.

106
00:03:48.645 --> 00:03:51.480
Fuck me!

107
00:03:51.481 --> 00:03:53.690
Uh. it's... it's in. It's just
so we can give you antibiotics.

108
00:03:53.691 --> 00:03:55.192
Oh.

109
00:03:55.193 --> 00:03:57.069
That hurt just as bad
as when I got shot.

110
00:03:57.070 --> 00:03:58.570
You put in an IO?

111
00:03:58.571 --> 00:04:00.155
Yeah.

112
00:04:00.156 --> 00:04:01.490
Um. don't worry. sir.

113
00:04:01.491 --> 00:04:02.824
There will be no more pain.

114
00:04:02.825 --> 00:04:03.867
Okay.

115
00:04:03.868 --> 00:04:05.702
Whitaker. um. team huddle.

116
00:04:07.538 --> 00:04:09.373
- Join us. will you?
- Mm-hmm.

117
00:04:09.374 --> 00:04:11.500
Oh. my God.

118
00:04:11.501 --> 00:04:14.544
Okay. um. why'd you do that?

119
00:04:14.545 --> 00:04:17.839
Dr. Robby said
everyone gets an IO.

120
00:04:17.840 --> 00:04:20.717
If they are unconscious
or unresponsive.

121
00:04:20.718 --> 00:04:23.387
If the patient is
awake and alert.

122
00:04:23.388 --> 00:04:25.597
it's just a standard
IV. not an IO.

123
00:04:25.598 --> 00:04:28.558
Unless it's a mime.
They can't scream.

124
00:04:28.559 --> 00:04:30.269
Lidocaine for the clown.

125
00:04:30.270 --> 00:04:31.561
More at the door.

126
00:04:31.562 --> 00:04:34.064
Is this ever gonna end?

127
00:04:34.065 --> 00:04:36.358
Pardon. Coming through.

128
00:04:36.359 --> 00:04:38.235
Bleed and bandage
it. Bring him out.

129
00:04:38.236 --> 00:04:40.028
To the other side?

130
00:04:40.029 --> 00:04:41.738
Ah. too much blood.

131
00:04:41.739 --> 00:04:43.365
Move that kelly to the
right a little bit.

132
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:45.033
- Any better?
- Not really.

133
00:04:45.034 --> 00:04:46.660
Radial pulse?
- Still has it.

134
00:04:46.661 --> 00:04:47.828
Maybe a little weaker.

135
00:04:47.829 --> 00:04:48.829
I can try and give you a bubble.

136
00:04:48.830 --> 00:04:50.623
Yeah. yeah. go for it.

137
00:04:52.166 --> 00:04:53.750
No. nothing. I'm
not seeing anything.

138
00:04:53.751 --> 00:04:56.420
Okay. let's bag him. I
want to prep the neck.

139
00:04:56.421 --> 00:04:57.796
You don't have a bougie.

140
00:04:57.797 --> 00:04:59.881
I have an 11 blade and a prayer.

141
00:04:59.882 --> 00:05:01.550
Without a bougie. you could
create a false passage

142
00:05:01.551 --> 00:05:03.135
on top of the
trachea and kill him.

143
00:05:03.136 --> 00:05:04.928
- You're doing a crike?
- Yep.

144
00:05:04.929 --> 00:05:08.223
No skin hooks. no
bougie... old school.

145
00:05:08.224 --> 00:05:09.850
I got a tactical
airway in my bag here.

146
00:05:09.851 --> 00:05:11.935
- What is that?
- It's a control crike kit.

147
00:05:11.936 --> 00:05:13.395
Oh. that's perfect.

148
00:05:13.396 --> 00:05:15.063
Use that on the battlefield.

149
00:05:15.064 --> 00:05:17.107
Works in the pitch-dark
when you're under fire.

150
00:05:17.108 --> 00:05:18.942
I can do these with
my eyes closed.

151
00:05:18.943 --> 00:05:20.944
For you.

152
00:05:20.945 --> 00:05:23.405
Okay.

153
00:05:23.406 --> 00:05:25.782
The knife leaves a
trach hook behind.

154
00:05:25.783 --> 00:05:27.784
so you can't miss. right?

155
00:05:27.785 --> 00:05:29.995
Just...

156
00:05:29.996 --> 00:05:31.955
good.

157
00:05:31.956 --> 00:05:35.751
You slide in the introducer.

158
00:05:35.752 --> 00:05:36.877
Okay.

159
00:05:36.878 --> 00:05:39.379
Feel the tracheal rings. Good.

160
00:05:39.380 --> 00:05:41.256
Bob's your uncle.

161
00:05:41.257 --> 00:05:44.134
- That was incredibly fast.
- Eh...

162
00:05:44.135 --> 00:05:45.719
Balloon is up.

163
00:05:45.720 --> 00:05:48.348
- Why don't we stock these?
- No room in the budget.

164
00:05:50.558 --> 00:05:52.476
Yellow on end-tidal.

165
00:05:52.477 --> 00:05:54.644
- It's okay now?
- Yeah.

166
00:05:54.645 --> 00:05:58.607
Thank you. Dr. Abbot.

167
00:05:58.608 --> 00:06:00.942
Okay. let's pack the
oral cavity with Kerlix

168
00:06:00.943 --> 00:06:02.861
and see how fast Head and Neck
can take him up to the OR.

169
00:06:02.862 --> 00:06:04.279
Great job. everybody.

170
00:06:04.280 --> 00:06:05.489
What else do you
got in your go bag?

171
00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:07.492
Oh. just wait and see.

172
00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:43.110
Javadi. this is Sally.

173
00:06:43.111 --> 00:06:44.444
What does she need?

174
00:06:44.445 --> 00:06:46.196
Gunshot wound to
the back at T11.

175
00:06:46.197 --> 00:06:48.448
Good pulse. but probable
spinal cord injury.

176
00:06:48.449 --> 00:06:52.327
- Can you move your legs?
- I'm trying.

177
00:06:52.328 --> 00:06:53.703
Am I paralyzed?

178
00:06:53.704 --> 00:06:55.247
There's some hope for recovery.

179
00:06:55.248 --> 00:06:56.998
Keep her on the
backboard and monitor

180
00:06:56.999 --> 00:06:58.250
for intra-abdominal hemorrhage.

181
00:06:58.251 --> 00:07:00.335
and neuro-ICU will
triage to CT. okay?

182
00:07:00.336 --> 00:07:02.671
Sally. pinprick
right here. okay?

183
00:07:02.672 --> 00:07:05.090
Walsh knows about the case.
They're holding an OR.

184
00:07:05.091 --> 00:07:07.175
And the hits keep coming.

185
00:07:07.176 --> 00:07:09.344
Let's go.

186
00:07:09.345 --> 00:07:11.805
Who do you have?

187
00:07:11.806 --> 00:07:14.308
Semiconscious. only
responds to pain.

188
00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:17.561
Decent carotid.
- Strip him.

189
00:07:17.562 --> 00:07:19.646
Let's go.

190
00:07:19.647 --> 00:07:21.731
Ah. left upper-quadrant
entrance.

191
00:07:23.067 --> 00:07:24.401
Hold him down.

192
00:07:24.402 --> 00:07:25.777
Grab his foot! Grab his foot!

193
00:07:25.778 --> 00:07:28.572
Whoa. gun! Gun! He's
going for his gun!

194
00:07:28.573 --> 00:07:30.198
Get down. get down.

195
00:07:31.868 --> 00:07:34.245
Stay down. Stay down.

196
00:07:37.790 --> 00:07:39.916
Sig P365 9 mil.

197
00:07:39.917 --> 00:07:42.335
- Driver's license?
- He just got here.

198
00:07:42.336 --> 00:07:44.046
Not responding to pain now.

199
00:07:45.423 --> 00:07:47.424
All clear.

200
00:07:47.425 --> 00:07:49.176
- You sure?
- He's unconscious.

201
00:07:49.177 --> 00:07:51.094
Everybody back to work.

202
00:07:51.095 --> 00:07:52.846
Agonal breathing.
He needs an airway.

203
00:07:52.847 --> 00:07:55.223
- Working on an IO.
- Drawing up ketamine and sux.

204
00:07:55.224 --> 00:07:56.600
Here. have at it.

205
00:07:56.601 --> 00:07:58.602
Concealed carry permit.

206
00:07:58.603 --> 00:08:00.395
We'll run his ID.

207
00:08:00.396 --> 00:08:02.397
These wounds are
too big for a 9.

208
00:08:02.398 --> 00:08:03.773
Failed IO.

209
00:08:03.774 --> 00:08:05.734
Guy's huge. Needle
won't reach the bone.

210
00:08:05.735 --> 00:08:07.402
He needs induction
meds and blood.

211
00:08:07.403 --> 00:08:08.778
I'm having the
same problem here.

212
00:08:08.779 --> 00:08:09.946
I don't see anything
usable for an IV.

213
00:08:09.947 --> 00:08:11.615
- Robby.
- What?

214
00:08:11.616 --> 00:08:14.284
Guy needs access. but the
IO won't reach the humerus.

215
00:08:14.285 --> 00:08:16.286
Proximal tibia?

216
00:08:16.287 --> 00:08:18.121
Yes?

217
00:08:18.122 --> 00:08:19.873
Yeah.

218
00:08:19.874 --> 00:08:21.291
Tibia's not great access.

219
00:08:21.292 --> 00:08:22.792
You can only get a liter
an hour down there.

220
00:08:22.793 --> 00:08:24.085
You get what you get.

221
00:08:26.380 --> 00:08:28.632
God damn it!

222
00:08:28.633 --> 00:08:30.509
Whatever that is. can
you please turn it off?

223
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:33.094
I can't hear myself think!
- Stable for the ICU.

224
00:08:33.095 --> 00:08:35.597
Get her up. I'll be
right fucking back.

225
00:08:35.598 --> 00:08:36.806
Copy that.

226
00:08:44.273 --> 00:08:46.149
I already have one.
Keep that away from me.

227
00:08:46.150 --> 00:08:47.859
It's not for you.

228
00:08:52.657 --> 00:08:54.199
<i>This is the monitoring center.</i>

229
00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:56.535
<i>We see that you're not
in your inclusion zone.</i>

230
00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:58.328
<i>Do you have permission...</i>

231
00:09:02.083 --> 00:09:05.418
- Show's over.
- Uh...

232
00:09:05.419 --> 00:09:07.754
are you gonna get
in trouble for that?

233
00:09:07.755 --> 00:09:09.507
Probably.

234
00:09:25.064 --> 00:09:26.524
Hey.

235
00:09:28.192 --> 00:09:30.193
What's going on out there?

236
00:09:30.194 --> 00:09:34.906
A lot of people were
hurt at the festival.

237
00:09:34.907 --> 00:09:37.534
I need to use the bathroom.

238
00:09:37.535 --> 00:09:41.037
- I told him to use the sink.
- What is wrong with you?

239
00:09:41.038 --> 00:09:42.872
Would you rather I
take him out there?

240
00:09:42.873 --> 00:09:46.042
Hang on. I'll be
right back. okay?

241
00:09:52.758 --> 00:09:55.385
Here.

242
00:09:55.386 --> 00:09:57.554
- What's that?
- It's a urinal.

243
00:09:57.555 --> 00:10:01.225
You pee in it.
- I think I'll just hold it in.

244
00:10:04.312 --> 00:10:06.688
Pull out. I found a 4 blade.

245
00:10:06.689 --> 00:10:09.482
This is better.

246
00:10:09.483 --> 00:10:10.900
Shit.

247
00:10:10.901 --> 00:10:13.486
I lost the light. The
battery must be dead.

248
00:10:13.487 --> 00:10:15.238
This one's dead. too.

249
00:10:15.239 --> 00:10:17.407
Anybody have a laryngoscope
with a light that still works?

250
00:10:17.408 --> 00:10:18.908
- We will check.
- Check quick.

251
00:10:18.909 --> 00:10:20.410
This guy's paralytics
are wearing off.

252
00:10:20.411 --> 00:10:21.995
Keep bagging. Give
me a 7.0 ET tube.

253
00:10:21.996 --> 00:10:23.371
He's a big guy. He needs an 8.

254
00:10:23.372 --> 00:10:25.081
- Not for this.
- Number 7.

255
00:10:25.082 --> 00:10:28.668
- What are you doing?
- Tactile intubation.

256
00:10:28.669 --> 00:10:32.422
My index finger goes
into the vallecula.

257
00:10:32.423 --> 00:10:36.426
And my middle finger will guide
the tube past the epiglottis.

258
00:10:36.427 --> 00:10:37.927
But if you hit the
esophagus. he's toast.

259
00:10:37.928 --> 00:10:39.471
You told us never to
pass a tube unless we see

260
00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:41.598
the vocal cords.
- Correct. Not today.

261
00:10:41.599 --> 00:10:43.224
If I stay in the midline.

262
00:10:43.225 --> 00:10:45.435
I should be able to
get it past the cords.

263
00:10:45.436 --> 00:10:47.270
Okay.

264
00:10:47.271 --> 00:10:50.440
Balloon up. Bag him.

265
00:10:50.441 --> 00:10:53.276
- Looks good on the end-tidal.
- Slick move. boss.

266
00:10:53.277 --> 00:10:54.819
No pulse. Start compressions.

267
00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:56.238
OK. Get him up.

268
00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:01.284
Try to get him back
with two liters.

269
00:11:01.285 --> 00:11:03.912
That is as much as we
can afford per patient.

270
00:11:03.913 --> 00:11:06.039
Leg is too slow; upper
arm is five times as fast.

271
00:11:06.040 --> 00:11:08.291
Best that we can do. Keep
at it. We'll get him back.

272
00:11:08.292 --> 00:11:10.378
Robby. need help here!

273
00:11:12.505 --> 00:11:14.130
- Langdon!
- Keep squeezing.

274
00:11:19.804 --> 00:11:21.388
How are you making out?

275
00:11:21.389 --> 00:11:23.723
Lots of emails
and photos coming in

276
00:11:23.724 --> 00:11:25.266
from concerned families.

277
00:11:25.267 --> 00:11:26.643
It'll be easier
once they've entered

278
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:28.228
every patient's MCI number.

279
00:11:28.229 --> 00:11:30.230
Here we go. Look familiar?

280
00:11:30.231 --> 00:11:32.232
MCI-7.

281
00:11:32.233 --> 00:11:33.983
His name is Vincent Rivera.

282
00:11:33.984 --> 00:11:36.319
He must have had friends
or family in the cafeteria

283
00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:38.363
who sent in the photo.

284
00:11:38.364 --> 00:11:40.991
I'll text them we're coming.

285
00:11:43.035 --> 00:11:45.161
- What are you doing?
- Giving this guy a chance.

286
00:11:45.162 --> 00:11:47.455
He needs a big central
line for fast transfusion.

287
00:11:47.456 --> 00:11:49.165
You can't do an IJ
without an ultrasound.

288
00:11:49.166 --> 00:11:50.959
especially on a guy this big.
- You'll kill him

289
00:11:50.960 --> 00:11:52.627
if you collapse a lung
or hit the carotid.

290
00:11:52.628 --> 00:11:54.003
I'm not doing an IJ.

291
00:11:54.004 --> 00:11:56.172
Unhook that blood
line. Bring it up here.

292
00:11:56.173 --> 00:12:00.677
This is a supraclavicular
subclavian.

293
00:12:00.678 --> 00:12:02.178
If you have to go in blind.

294
00:12:02.179 --> 00:12:05.598
this is the only safe way
to access a giant vein.

295
00:12:05.599 --> 00:12:09.185
And hold compressions.

296
00:12:09.186 --> 00:12:10.979
A centimeter

297
00:12:10.980 --> 00:12:14.190
from the lateral head of
the sternocleidomastoid.

298
00:12:14.191 --> 00:12:16.526
a centimeter off the clavicle.

299
00:12:16.527 --> 00:12:20.531
aiming at the
contralateral nipple.

300
00:12:22.450 --> 00:12:23.868
I'm in.

301
00:12:25.703 --> 00:12:28.788
Okay. resume compressions.

302
00:12:28.789 --> 00:12:31.500
And squeeze blood.

303
00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:34.711
- Where'd you learn that?
- RAP" podcast.

304
00:12:34.712 --> 00:12:37.213
We'll be ready for a second
unit in under a minute.

305
00:12:37.214 --> 00:12:38.923
Boom.

306
00:12:38.924 --> 00:12:42.093
Okay. not too much blood on
your dressing. Mr. Grayson.

307
00:12:42.094 --> 00:12:44.053
You're looking good.

308
00:12:44.054 --> 00:12:46.431
Mr. Grayson? Hey. Mr. Grayson!

309
00:12:46.432 --> 00:12:47.766
Oh.

310
00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:49.768
Oh. I must've dozed off.

311
00:12:49.769 --> 00:12:51.519
This is like a bad dream.

312
00:12:51.520 --> 00:12:54.230
Yeah. no kidding.

313
00:12:54.231 --> 00:12:57.901
You. um... did you happen
to see who shot you?

314
00:12:57.902 --> 00:12:59.569
No.

315
00:12:59.570 --> 00:13:01.738
But I heard the shots.

316
00:13:01.739 --> 00:13:05.617
They just kept coming.
gunshots and screaming.

317
00:13:05.618 --> 00:13:07.744
I'm never gonna get
that out of my head.

318
00:13:07.745 --> 00:13:09.913
GSW to the right
inguinal region.

319
00:13:09.914 --> 00:13:11.039
Yeah.

320
00:13:11.040 --> 00:13:13.583
Uh. hi. I'm Dr. Whitaker.

321
00:13:13.584 --> 00:13:15.043
Carmen.

322
00:13:15.044 --> 00:13:16.544
It's. uh. nice to meet you.

323
00:13:16.545 --> 00:13:17.587
Uh...

324
00:13:17.588 --> 00:13:19.839
I'm just gonna take this.

325
00:13:19.840 --> 00:13:21.257
Okay.

326
00:13:21.258 --> 00:13:24.385
How's the pain?
- I can handle it.

327
00:13:24.386 --> 00:13:26.346
Okay.

328
00:13:26.347 --> 00:13:28.848
What does this... "tem-bleek"?
What does that mean?

329
00:13:28.849 --> 00:13:31.601
Tembleque... it's a coconut
pudding from Puerto Rico.

330
00:13:31.602 --> 00:13:34.270
We top it off with
canela... cinnamon.

331
00:13:34.271 --> 00:13:36.397
Okay. wow. So you
got a food truck?

332
00:13:36.398 --> 00:13:39.067
- Just a folding table for now.
- Pedal pulses are strong.

333
00:13:39.068 --> 00:13:40.652
Okay. let's start with
antibiotics. pain meds.

334
00:13:40.653 --> 00:13:42.278
and let's try to
stop this bleeding.

335
00:13:42.279 --> 00:13:44.280
Okay.

336
00:13:44.281 --> 00:13:45.657
Here we go.

337
00:13:45.658 --> 00:13:47.617
Okay. uh. could you take over?

338
00:13:47.618 --> 00:13:48.952
Thank you. thank you. thank you.

339
00:13:48.953 --> 00:13:51.496
Hey. hey. hey.

340
00:13:51.497 --> 00:13:54.290
Inguinal GSW with
active bleeding.

341
00:13:54.291 --> 00:13:56.084
Um. try an Israeli bandage.

342
00:13:56.085 --> 00:13:58.670
What if it bleeds through?
It's at the top of the leg.

343
00:13:58.671 --> 00:14:00.964
There's no room for a
tourniquet above the wound.

344
00:14:00.965 --> 00:14:04.968
Well. let's just hope the
hemostatic bandage works.

345
00:14:04.969 --> 00:14:06.845
Okay.

346
00:14:06.846 --> 00:14:08.847
Coming in. Good.

347
00:14:08.848 --> 00:14:10.974
Hey. so...

348
00:14:10.975 --> 00:14:12.308
coconut.

349
00:14:12.309 --> 00:14:14.060
Love coconut.

350
00:14:20.359 --> 00:14:21.943
- Kiara?
- Yes.

351
00:14:21.944 --> 00:14:23.611
This is Lupe.

352
00:14:23.612 --> 00:14:25.905
Whitney. You texted me.

353
00:14:25.906 --> 00:14:27.782
Let's take a walk over here.

354
00:14:27.783 --> 00:14:29.909
Can you tell us
your husband's name?

355
00:14:29.910 --> 00:14:31.662
Vincent Rivera.

356
00:14:33.163 --> 00:14:35.748
We're gonna show
you some photos.

357
00:14:35.749 --> 00:14:38.334
Can you tell us if
this is Vincent?

358
00:14:38.335 --> 00:14:41.213
- He's not talking?
- No. he's not.

359
00:14:45.175 --> 00:14:46.885
Yes. that's Vincent.

360
00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:49.220
Can I see him?

361
00:14:49.221 --> 00:14:52.140
Vincent had a
gunshot to the head.

362
00:14:52.141 --> 00:14:54.142
When he arrived here.

363
00:14:54.143 --> 00:14:57.271
there was no pulse or breathing.

364
00:14:59.189 --> 00:15:01.816
My husband is dead?

365
00:15:01.817 --> 00:15:04.027
- I'm so sorry.
- We're sorry.

366
00:15:04.028 --> 00:15:05.904
What about
my brother. Brian?

367
00:15:05.905 --> 00:15:08.197
Vincent and Brian went
to the festival together.

368
00:15:08.198 --> 00:15:09.699
Is my brother okay?

369
00:15:09.700 --> 00:15:11.034
Can you send us
his name and photo?

370
00:15:11.035 --> 00:15:12.702
I did.

371
00:15:12.703 --> 00:15:15.288
Okay. well. as of now. he's
not one of our fatalities.

372
00:15:15.289 --> 00:15:17.707
Do you have some relatives
or friends we can call

373
00:15:17.708 --> 00:15:19.876
to come be with you?

374
00:15:22.838 --> 00:15:25.257
Our kids are with my parents.

375
00:15:31.221 --> 00:15:34.474
- Second unit's in.
- Holding compressions.

376
00:15:34.475 --> 00:15:36.809
Carotid pulse... you feeling it?
- I'm feeling it.

377
00:15:36.810 --> 00:15:38.645
He goes right up to pre-op.

378
00:15:38.646 --> 00:15:40.563
Let's go. Let's go. I
need some help over here!

379
00:15:40.564 --> 00:15:43.107
Hey. Not a person of interest.

380
00:15:43.108 --> 00:15:44.943
Jewelry store owner. no priors.

381
00:15:44.944 --> 00:15:46.444
He's not our shooter.

382
00:15:46.445 --> 00:15:49.197
- You guys good in here?
- We got this.

383
00:15:49.198 --> 00:15:50.907
Take a two-hour lunch.

384
00:15:50.908 --> 00:15:52.533
I'm gonna go check on triage.

385
00:15:52.534 --> 00:15:54.577
We'll save a spot for you.

386
00:15:54.578 --> 00:15:55.912
Yellow gets a wheelchair.

387
00:15:55.913 --> 00:15:57.413
Hey. Ahmad. what
number are we up to?

388
00:15:57.414 --> 00:16:00.124
- 85 patients so far.
- Need a gurney for pink.

389
00:16:00.125 --> 00:16:02.627
- How are you guys doing?
- Still going strong.

390
00:16:02.628 --> 00:16:04.629
- Not bad. I guess.
- You guys are triaging great.

391
00:16:04.630 --> 00:16:06.089
Believe me. This is not easy.

392
00:16:06.090 --> 00:16:07.548
Not everybody can pull this off.

393
00:16:07.549 --> 00:16:08.925
Is this your half-time
locker room speech?

394
00:16:08.926 --> 00:16:10.218
Yeah. possibly.

395
00:16:10.219 --> 00:16:11.594
Are we winning or
losing the game?

396
00:16:11.595 --> 00:16:14.389
Too soon to tell.

397
00:16:14.390 --> 00:16:16.099
Come on. these heads
have to be up 30 degrees.

398
00:16:16.100 --> 00:16:18.017
Let's go.
- Got four back here.

399
00:16:19.603 --> 00:16:22.230
Through and through the head.

400
00:16:22.231 --> 00:16:24.065
No pulse. Black and white.

401
00:16:24.066 --> 00:16:26.943
Pink zone. Strong pulse.
Unresponsive. no obvious GSW.

402
00:16:26.944 --> 00:16:28.736
Red zone. GSW left chest.

403
00:16:28.737 --> 00:16:30.279
She was talking when we
first got in the truck.

404
00:16:30.280 --> 00:16:32.448
Weak carotid. unresponsive.

405
00:16:32.449 --> 00:16:33.700
There... there
was so much blood.

406
00:16:33.701 --> 00:16:36.869
I tried to stop it.
- Jake!

407
00:16:36.870 --> 00:16:39.622
Robby! Leah got shot!
It's really bad!

408
00:16:43.585 --> 00:16:45.461
I've been putting pressure
on the wound the whole time.

409
00:16:45.462 --> 00:16:46.796
Yeah. that's
good. That's good.

410
00:16:46.797 --> 00:16:48.297
Are you shot?
- I don't... maybe my leg.

411
00:16:48.298 --> 00:16:49.966
Most of this is her blood.

412
00:16:49.967 --> 00:16:52.468
- Somebody you know. boss?
- Yeah.

413
00:16:52.469 --> 00:16:54.137
- You got this?
- Yeah.

414
00:16:54.138 --> 00:16:56.639
Okay. come on. let's go.
Let's go. I got you. Come on.

415
00:16:56.640 --> 00:16:58.474
Ready? Pull.

416
00:17:05.190 --> 00:17:08.276
Jake. you can't stay with her.
- I have to.

417
00:17:08.277 --> 00:17:10.194
There's no room. and we need
to work on Leah right now.

418
00:17:10.195 --> 00:17:11.320
and you need to get
your leg checked.

419
00:17:11.321 --> 00:17:12.822
so please go sit down.

420
00:17:12.823 --> 00:17:14.032
Please come tell me
how she's doing. okay?

421
00:17:14.033 --> 00:17:16.993
Please?
- I will.

422
00:17:16.994 --> 00:17:19.245
- Jake?
- I-I'm okay.

423
00:17:19.246 --> 00:17:21.248
Leah's with Robby.

424
00:17:42.352 --> 00:17:44.771
- Can't feel carotid.
- Start compressions.

425
00:17:44.772 --> 00:17:46.105
Swap out with me.

426
00:17:46.106 --> 00:17:48.816
I need an IO. Hang
a unit of O-neg.

427
00:17:48.817 --> 00:17:50.693
Got the IO.

428
00:17:50.694 --> 00:17:52.487
- Leah?
- Yeah.

429
00:17:52.488 --> 00:17:55.531
- You need help over there?
- No. we're good.

430
00:17:55.532 --> 00:17:58.409
- That's Jake's girlfriend.
- Oh. shit.

431
00:17:58.410 --> 00:18:02.205
- Who's Jake?
- It's. like. Robby's stepson.

432
00:18:02.206 --> 00:18:03.831
I'll be right with you. sir.

433
00:18:03.832 --> 00:18:05.708
My mom would be very happy.

434
00:18:05.709 --> 00:18:07.543
She always says.
wear clean underwear

435
00:18:07.544 --> 00:18:10.505
in case you end up
in the hospital.

436
00:18:10.506 --> 00:18:13.382
Just let us know if anything
is too uncomfortable.

437
00:18:13.383 --> 00:18:15.760
- It's okay.
- This needs to be tighter.

438
00:18:15.761 --> 00:18:17.762
You bled through the
last one pretty fast.

439
00:18:17.763 --> 00:18:21.015
Try a 180-degree twist.
It'll put more pressure.

440
00:18:21.016 --> 00:18:22.350
Got it.

441
00:18:22.351 --> 00:18:24.018
I usually faint when
my blood gets drawn.

442
00:18:24.019 --> 00:18:25.645
Must be all the
adrenaline today.

443
00:18:25.646 --> 00:18:27.063
Whitaker?

444
00:18:27.064 --> 00:18:28.815
Old hippie's looking
pretty out of it.

445
00:18:28.816 --> 00:18:31.234
No. he's sleeping.

446
00:18:31.235 --> 00:18:34.654
- No response to pain.
- Shit.

447
00:18:34.655 --> 00:18:37.406
Uh. Mr. Grayson. Mr. Grayson.

448
00:18:37.407 --> 00:18:39.325
Could be a delayed head bleed.

449
00:18:39.326 --> 00:18:41.661
He's gonna need a head CT.

450
00:18:41.662 --> 00:18:44.747
He's not getting
one anytime soon.

451
00:18:44.748 --> 00:18:46.666
Equal and reactive.
No blown pupil.

452
00:18:46.667 --> 00:18:50.753
Santos. go get an attending.
- I'll try. but no promises.

453
00:18:50.754 --> 00:18:52.964
Excuse me. I think
I'm still bleeding.

454
00:18:52.965 --> 00:18:55.092
I'll be with you in a minute.

455
00:18:57.136 --> 00:18:59.096
Pleur-evac ready. Here you go.

456
00:19:01.807 --> 00:19:04.100
Princess. take over as primary.

457
00:19:04.101 --> 00:19:06.978
- What about Bridget?
- She's stuck in yellow.

458
00:19:06.979 --> 00:19:09.814
- Mel needs an attending.
- Find somebody who's free.

459
00:19:09.815 --> 00:19:11.649
- Let's get blood.
- Dr. Abbot. can you come...

460
00:19:11.650 --> 00:19:13.484
Gonna be a minute.

461
00:19:13.485 --> 00:19:15.820
- Dr. Walsh.
- Taking one up to the OR.

462
00:19:15.821 --> 00:19:17.947
Okay.

463
00:19:17.948 --> 00:19:20.324
Hey. I need a portable
pulse ox for Mr. Grayson.

464
00:19:20.325 --> 00:19:23.035
Here you go.

465
00:19:23.036 --> 00:19:25.037
Hey. what happened to
the kid in the wheelchair

466
00:19:25.038 --> 00:19:26.622
with the bloody right leg?

467
00:19:26.623 --> 00:19:28.916
No idea.

468
00:19:28.917 --> 00:19:31.460
Pinpoint pupils...
probable OD.

469
00:19:31.461 --> 00:19:32.962
Blood on his clothes wasn't his.

470
00:19:32.963 --> 00:19:35.548
- I'll grab some Narcan.
- Sublingual injection.

471
00:19:35.549 --> 00:19:36.799
Okay here?

472
00:19:36.800 --> 00:19:39.051
Uh. looks like a
opioid overdose.

473
00:19:39.052 --> 00:19:40.429
How's Robby with Leah?

474
00:19:42.139 --> 00:19:45.892
If this guy doesn't wake up.
we'll check for occult trauma.

475
00:19:45.893 --> 00:19:47.894
1.400 of blood out the
chest. First unit's in.

476
00:19:47.895 --> 00:19:49.145
Squeeze in a second unit fast.

477
00:19:49.146 --> 00:19:50.813
and then we'll do
another pulse check.

478
00:19:50.814 --> 00:19:52.982
- She's needs a second line?
- For FFP and platelets.

479
00:19:52.983 --> 00:19:54.525
You sure. Robby?

480
00:19:54.526 --> 00:19:56.986
Sophie. get the plasma.

481
00:19:56.987 --> 00:19:58.779
I'm gonna take
over compressions.

482
00:19:58.780 --> 00:20:00.823
And swap.

483
00:20:00.824 --> 00:20:02.658
<i>Social worker to
the south corridor.</i>

484
00:20:02.659 --> 00:20:04.453
<i>Social worker to
the south corridor.</i>

485
00:20:11.919 --> 00:20:14.670
Jamie. wheelchair.

486
00:20:14.671 --> 00:20:16.130
You can't be in here.

487
00:20:16.131 --> 00:20:17.173
They're working
on my girlfriend.

488
00:20:17.174 --> 00:20:18.841
I need to see what's going on.

489
00:20:18.842 --> 00:20:20.301
What's going on is. you're
losing a lot of blood.

490
00:20:20.302 --> 00:20:21.719
You're gonna pass out
if we don't stop it.

491
00:20:21.720 --> 00:20:23.054
No. I'm not moving.
man! Leave me alone!

492
00:20:23.055 --> 00:20:24.472
Jake. get in the
damn wheelchair.

493
00:20:24.473 --> 00:20:26.266
- No!
- Now! Go!

494
00:20:32.314 --> 00:20:35.691
Welcome back. sir.
You're in the ER at PTMC.

495
00:20:35.692 --> 00:20:38.527
- What's your name?
- Martin.

496
00:20:38.528 --> 00:20:41.697
What'd you take. Martin?
You overdosed at Pitt Fest.

497
00:20:41.698 --> 00:20:43.199
I took one Percocet
so I could dance.

498
00:20:43.200 --> 00:20:44.784
I've got a bad knee.

499
00:20:44.785 --> 00:20:46.702
- Where'd you get the pill?
- From a friend.

500
00:20:46.703 --> 00:20:48.371
Okay. while you were
overdosing from the fentanyl

501
00:20:48.372 --> 00:20:50.873
in a fake pill. there was a
mass shooting at Pitt Fest.

502
00:20:50.874 --> 00:20:53.167
- What?
- Hey. Samira.

503
00:20:53.168 --> 00:20:54.710
see if you can go help
Mel in the yellow zone.

504
00:20:54.711 --> 00:20:56.712
Take my new friend
Martin with you.

505
00:20:56.713 --> 00:20:59.216
Javadi. roll with me.

506
00:21:05.222 --> 00:21:06.764
Two units packed cells in.

507
00:21:06.765 --> 00:21:09.433
FFP still going?
- Almost there.

508
00:21:09.434 --> 00:21:12.728
Okay. holding compressions.

509
00:21:12.729 --> 00:21:14.605
Can't feel carotid.

510
00:21:14.606 --> 00:21:15.898
No femoral.

511
00:21:15.899 --> 00:21:18.067
Resuming compressions.

512
00:21:18.068 --> 00:21:21.112
- What's your next move. boss?
- Platelets. another unit.

513
00:21:21.113 --> 00:21:22.863
And then we can transfuse
her with her own blood

514
00:21:22.864 --> 00:21:24.740
from the Pleur-evac
to get ahead.

515
00:21:24.741 --> 00:21:26.367
Hang the cell saver.

516
00:21:26.368 --> 00:21:28.160
- Squeeze all this in?
- No.

517
00:21:28.161 --> 00:21:29.870
Three-way stopcock
on a 60-cc syringe.

518
00:21:29.871 --> 00:21:31.247
I'll push-pull.
- Okay.

519
00:21:31.248 --> 00:21:33.834
Not exactly in our mass
casualty game plan.

520
00:21:37.254 --> 00:21:39.380
I tried. No
attendings available.

521
00:21:39.381 --> 00:21:40.756
Okay.

522
00:21:44.344 --> 00:21:45.928
All right.

523
00:21:45.929 --> 00:21:47.930
Okay. those look
pretty superficial.

524
00:21:47.931 --> 00:21:50.349
Might've been fragments from
a ricochet off the ground.

525
00:21:50.350 --> 00:21:53.185
Lost a lot of blood. but
you're gonna be okay. bro.

526
00:21:53.186 --> 00:21:54.895
It's not bad. Just put me
back in the wheelchair.

527
00:21:54.896 --> 00:21:56.439
No. no. stay in bed
with your leg up.

528
00:21:56.440 --> 00:21:57.815
We don't want you
oozing to death.

529
00:21:57.816 --> 00:21:59.317
Samira. what you got?

530
00:21:59.318 --> 00:22:00.901
Opiate OD needs
observation after Narcan.

531
00:22:00.902 --> 00:22:02.486
Ugh. boring. No. thank you.

532
00:22:02.487 --> 00:22:04.280
Mel. how's Ganja Grayson?

533
00:22:04.281 --> 00:22:08.117
Um. we can put him in pink
while he waits for ICU.

534
00:22:08.118 --> 00:22:10.287
Okay. one second.

535
00:22:11.830 --> 00:22:14.623
- What are you doing?
- I'm checking the retina.

536
00:22:14.624 --> 00:22:16.959
- For detachment?
- For intracranial pressure

537
00:22:16.960 --> 00:22:19.670
by measuring the optic
nerve sheath. which is...

538
00:22:19.671 --> 00:22:21.255
holy shit... 10 millimeters.

539
00:22:21.256 --> 00:22:23.132
- What's normal? 5?
- Yeah. 5.

540
00:22:23.133 --> 00:22:24.508
It's an intracranial bleed.

541
00:22:24.509 --> 00:22:25.843
The pressure's been building up.

542
00:22:25.844 --> 00:22:27.470
There's no blown pupil.
- Yeah. not yet.

543
00:22:27.471 --> 00:22:29.388
But if he keeps bleeding in
his skull. he's gonna die.

544
00:22:29.389 --> 00:22:32.475
Yeah. he needs a one-inch.
uh. burr hole in his...

545
00:22:32.476 --> 00:22:33.934
with a cranial drill.

546
00:22:33.935 --> 00:22:35.644
I'm just gonna see if
Neurosurgery's here.

547
00:22:35.645 --> 00:22:38.397
We don't have time
to wait for Neuro.

548
00:22:38.398 --> 00:22:40.775
I got Betadine and
a 10-cc syringe.

549
00:22:40.776 --> 00:22:42.234
Should we intubate.
hyperventilate?

550
00:22:42.235 --> 00:22:44.487
Mannitol decreases ICP.

551
00:22:45.822 --> 00:22:48.074
- Holy shit!
- What the hell?

552
00:22:49.910 --> 00:22:52.161
Relieving intracranial pressure

553
00:22:52.162 --> 00:22:53.746
so he doesn't die.

554
00:22:53.747 --> 00:22:56.665
With an IO drill?

555
00:22:56.666 --> 00:22:58.000
That's sick.

556
00:22:58.001 --> 00:22:59.460
I get the next one.

557
00:22:59.461 --> 00:23:02.130
Long as it's not on me.

558
00:23:05.133 --> 00:23:06.801
Dana. is Neurosurgery down here?

559
00:23:06.802 --> 00:23:08.844
Ask Princess.

560
00:23:08.845 --> 00:23:10.846
- Princess...
- Cardiothoracic ICU.

561
00:23:10.847 --> 00:23:13.307
- I need a neurosurgeon.
- They're all in the OR.

562
00:23:13.308 --> 00:23:16.018
Dr. Walsh. I have an epidural
in the north corridor

563
00:23:16.019 --> 00:23:17.186
with an elevated ICP.

564
00:23:17.187 --> 00:23:18.854
Is there a blown pupil?

565
00:23:18.855 --> 00:23:21.232
No. but a 10-millimeter optic
sheath on the ultrasound.

566
00:23:21.233 --> 00:23:23.151
We need a burr hole.

567
00:23:25.487 --> 00:23:27.363
What the fuck?

568
00:23:27.364 --> 00:23:29.407
Draining the ICH with an EZ-IO.

569
00:23:29.408 --> 00:23:31.200
40 cc's out so far.

570
00:23:31.201 --> 00:23:33.661
- Like she said. what the fuck?
- There was a case report

571
00:23:33.662 --> 00:23:35.663
in the 2022 "Journal
of Emergency Medicine."

572
00:23:35.664 --> 00:23:37.373
Patient survive?

573
00:23:37.374 --> 00:23:39.041
Went home neurologically intact.

574
00:23:39.042 --> 00:23:40.793
The optic sheath
is back to normal.

575
00:23:40.794 --> 00:23:42.795
Starting purposeful movements.

576
00:23:42.796 --> 00:23:45.506
- Ready to intubate.
- Propofol. rock. and mannitol.

577
00:23:45.507 --> 00:23:47.883
I'll let Neurosurgery know.
We'll get him up ASAP.

578
00:23:47.884 --> 00:23:50.302
- Incredible save.
- If he lives.

579
00:23:50.303 --> 00:23:53.514
- Third unit's in.
- Okay. pulse check.

580
00:23:56.059 --> 00:23:57.810
I think I'm feeling a femoral.

581
00:23:57.811 --> 00:23:59.395
I got a carotid.

582
00:23:59.396 --> 00:24:01.522
Emery. I got a chest case.
needs to go to the OR.

583
00:24:01.523 --> 00:24:03.399
I saw you doing
CPR on this girl.

584
00:24:03.400 --> 00:24:04.733
Two liters out of
the left chest.

585
00:24:04.734 --> 00:24:06.610
Got a pulse back after
three packed cells.

586
00:24:06.611 --> 00:24:09.072
600 out of the cell
saver. 2 of FFP.

587
00:24:12.909 --> 00:24:15.077
- I'm not feeling it.
- Check the carotid.

588
00:24:19.541 --> 00:24:22.418
- Nothing. Sorry.
- Resume compressions.

589
00:24:22.419 --> 00:24:24.295
No. no. we should take her
up. She just had a pulse.

590
00:24:24.296 --> 00:24:26.213
Not now. We need a
pulse to go to the OR.

591
00:24:26.214 --> 00:24:28.382
Call me if anything changes.
- Got a Pink coming in.

592
00:24:28.383 --> 00:24:29.967
Do we have any more whole
blood from the donors?

593
00:24:29.968 --> 00:24:31.260
- Think so.
- Okay. get another unit

594
00:24:31.261 --> 00:24:32.470
that's got platelets and plasma.

595
00:24:32.471 --> 00:24:35.264
It'll help her clot.
- Got it.

596
00:24:35.265 --> 00:24:36.932
Four units.

597
00:24:36.933 --> 00:24:38.601
Blood is for the
ones we can save.

598
00:24:38.602 --> 00:24:40.269
She is right on the edge.

599
00:24:40.270 --> 00:24:42.230
One more can make
the difference.

600
00:24:46.693 --> 00:24:48.028
I'm in.

601
00:24:50.697 --> 00:24:52.364
Uh. end-tidal looks good.

602
00:24:52.365 --> 00:24:54.116
Okay. OR team can
take it from here.

603
00:24:54.117 --> 00:24:55.743
We need to check on the others.

604
00:24:55.744 --> 00:24:57.913
- I should get back to Pink.
- Stay strong. Crash.

605
00:24:59.456 --> 00:25:01.790
Uh. hemostatic bandage
still in place.

606
00:25:01.791 --> 00:25:04.418
How you doing. Carmen?
- Not so great.

607
00:25:04.419 --> 00:25:07.254
Okay. let's see.

608
00:25:07.255 --> 00:25:09.673
- Looks arterial.
- Agreed.

609
00:25:09.674 --> 00:25:11.342
Can you stop it?

610
00:25:11.343 --> 00:25:14.470
- Uh. direct pressure for now.
- Yeah.

611
00:25:14.471 --> 00:25:16.347
We may have a
junctional tourniquet

612
00:25:16.348 --> 00:25:17.848
in the disaster supplies.

613
00:25:17.849 --> 00:25:19.517
Can you get that? Cool.

614
00:25:19.518 --> 00:25:21.101
Um...

615
00:25:21.102 --> 00:25:22.686
Whitaker. in the meantime.
just put pressure on it.

616
00:25:22.687 --> 00:25:24.647
Try and stop the bleeding.
- For how long?

617
00:25:24.648 --> 00:25:26.524
As long as it takes.

618
00:25:26.525 --> 00:25:28.817
- He bled through his Kerlix.
- Um...

619
00:25:28.818 --> 00:25:30.986
elastic... elastic
pressure dressing.

620
00:25:30.987 --> 00:25:33.155
Yep.
- Okay. got it.

621
00:25:33.156 --> 00:25:35.491
All right.

622
00:25:35.492 --> 00:25:38.160
Got a better bandage. and
we're gonna elevate your leg.

623
00:25:38.161 --> 00:25:39.995
Do you know what's happening
with my girlfriend?

624
00:25:39.996 --> 00:25:41.664
Her name is Leah. She
was shot in the chest.

625
00:25:41.665 --> 00:25:43.415
I'm sorry. We have
a ton of patients.

626
00:25:43.416 --> 00:25:45.167
and they're only
marked by number.

627
00:25:45.168 --> 00:25:47.753
Robby and Dana were working
on her... they were doing CPR.

628
00:25:47.754 --> 00:25:49.630
How do you know Robby and Dana?

629
00:25:49.631 --> 00:25:51.340
Robby and my mom were
together for a couple years.

630
00:25:51.341 --> 00:25:53.968
and I would... I would
come. and I'd hang out here.

631
00:25:53.969 --> 00:25:56.428
Well. I'm sure if
they're helping her.

632
00:25:56.429 --> 00:25:58.347
then she's in great hands.

633
00:25:58.348 --> 00:26:00.432
Can you check for me. please?

634
00:26:00.433 --> 00:26:02.811
Sure. Of course. Just
after I finish this.

635
00:26:07.148 --> 00:26:10.067
Well. there's no
additional bleeding.

636
00:26:10.068 --> 00:26:11.819
Strong pulse.

637
00:26:11.820 --> 00:26:15.155
Two grams of Ancef running in.

638
00:26:15.156 --> 00:26:16.950
Can you. uh. spread
your fingers?

639
00:26:19.077 --> 00:26:22.705
Uh. no. like this.

640
00:26:22.706 --> 00:26:25.416
Are you okay?

641
00:26:25.417 --> 00:26:27.209
Found the junctional tourniquet.

642
00:26:27.210 --> 00:26:30.130
Um. okay. Uh. I'll
be right back.

643
00:26:33.883 --> 00:26:36.260
How much blood you pushing
off the cell saver?

644
00:26:36.261 --> 00:26:38.554
Every last drop.

645
00:26:38.555 --> 00:26:40.389
O-neg. Monitor the pulse.

646
00:26:40.390 --> 00:26:44.144
She's stable for trauma
ICU if an OR's not ready.

647
00:26:54.779 --> 00:26:56.572
How many units so far?

648
00:26:56.573 --> 00:26:59.575
Four. plus the cell saver.

649
00:26:59.576 --> 00:27:02.077
- Last one?
- Getting backed up out there.

650
00:27:02.078 --> 00:27:03.662
I don't know.

651
00:27:03.663 --> 00:27:05.748
Dana. why don't we
try a little TXA?

652
00:27:05.749 --> 00:27:07.541
1.000 milligrams of TXA
might help her clot.

653
00:27:07.542 --> 00:27:09.460
Got it.

654
00:27:09.461 --> 00:27:12.421
Bullet tore through her heart.

655
00:27:12.422 --> 00:27:13.756
Anyone else with
a wound like this

656
00:27:13.757 --> 00:27:15.257
is pronounced dead in the field.

657
00:27:15.258 --> 00:27:16.759
You can't keep up
with the blood loss.

658
00:27:16.760 --> 00:27:18.260
If she was our only patient.

659
00:27:18.261 --> 00:27:20.220
we'd do a thoracotomy.
maybe ECMO.

660
00:27:20.221 --> 00:27:22.932
But even then. I doubt
we'd get her back.

661
00:27:25.185 --> 00:27:26.769
We're gonna lose
ten other patients

662
00:27:26.770 --> 00:27:30.105
if you put all your efforts
into saving this girl.

663
00:27:33.610 --> 00:27:35.778
Got the TXA.

664
00:27:35.779 --> 00:27:36.987
Okay. push it fast.

665
00:27:36.988 --> 00:27:38.781
and we'll do
another pulse check.

666
00:27:38.782 --> 00:27:41.242
And then can you get me a
vascular Doppler too. please?

667
00:27:44.996 --> 00:27:47.706
GSW to the chest. faint pulse.

668
00:27:47.707 --> 00:27:50.209
Intubation. IO. chest
tube. and a unit of blood.

669
00:27:50.210 --> 00:27:51.293
Copy that.

670
00:27:51.294 --> 00:27:52.961
<i>All nonessential personnel.</i>

671
00:27:52.962 --> 00:27:54.963
<i>please report to the
patient waiting room.</i>

672
00:27:54.964 --> 00:27:56.757
<i>All nonessential personnel.</i>

673
00:27:56.758 --> 00:27:59.134
<i>please report to the
patient waiting room.</i>

674
00:28:03.973 --> 00:28:05.433
Anything I can do?

675
00:28:08.812 --> 00:28:11.522
You can check on Shen and
Ellis in the ambulance bay.

676
00:28:11.523 --> 00:28:12.774
On it.

677
00:28:17.404 --> 00:28:18.654
Whitaker. lay down
some fresh gauze

678
00:28:18.655 --> 00:28:19.988
so we can assess the hemostasis.

679
00:28:19.989 --> 00:28:22.157
Yep. How you doing. Carmen?

680
00:28:22.158 --> 00:28:24.159
I'm hanging in there.

681
00:28:24.160 --> 00:28:25.619
You want the circle
of compression

682
00:28:25.620 --> 00:28:27.705
directly over the wound.

683
00:28:27.706 --> 00:28:29.249
Tighten.

684
00:28:31.126 --> 00:28:33.460
Inflate the balloon. Come
on. pump it up. Whittaker.

685
00:28:33.461 --> 00:28:37.131
- Uh. how much pressure?
- Until the bleeding stops.

686
00:28:37.132 --> 00:28:38.966
Uh. excuse me. ma'am.

687
00:28:38.967 --> 00:28:40.843
Ma'am. where are you...

688
00:28:40.844 --> 00:28:42.344
uh. Whittaker. stay on this.

689
00:28:42.345 --> 00:28:45.180
Ma'am? Ma'am?

690
00:28:45.181 --> 00:28:47.933
Do you need something?

691
00:28:47.934 --> 00:28:49.060
Are you...

692
00:28:52.522 --> 00:28:55.023
I need one more O-neg.

693
00:28:55.024 --> 00:28:58.360
Hey. do you have any
O-positive over there?

694
00:28:58.361 --> 00:29:01.488
This guy bled
through his bandage.

695
00:29:01.489 --> 00:29:04.616
<i>All available transport
to the ER immediately.</i>

696
00:29:04.617 --> 00:29:08.162
<i>All available transport
to the ER immediately.</i>

697
00:29:08.163 --> 00:29:09.997
Okay.

698
00:29:09.998 --> 00:29:12.040
Let me just... just
put your arm like that.

699
00:29:12.041 --> 00:29:13.710
Just keep your hand like that.

700
00:29:16.004 --> 00:29:17.379
Just...

701
00:29:17.380 --> 00:29:19.173
How we doing out here?

702
00:29:19.174 --> 00:29:21.049
Dancing as fast as we can.

703
00:29:21.050 --> 00:29:23.886
Pretty sure I'm past my
union-mandated bathroom break.

704
00:29:23.887 --> 00:29:26.013
I never should have
had that second coffee.

705
00:29:28.558 --> 00:29:30.893
Hey. son. ER's closed
unless you're injured.

706
00:29:30.894 --> 00:29:33.353
Oh. my mom's inside. I
need to take her home.

707
00:29:33.354 --> 00:29:36.690
- David?
- Mom?

708
00:29:36.691 --> 00:29:39.276
You're the kid? You
need to come with me.

709
00:29:39.277 --> 00:29:41.069
Hey! Grab him!
- Wait. David! Stop!

710
00:29:41.070 --> 00:29:43.071
- Grab him!
- What are you doing?

711
00:29:43.072 --> 00:29:45.032
- Stay down!
- Don't hurt him!

712
00:29:45.033 --> 00:29:46.325
What the hell's going on?

713
00:29:46.326 --> 00:29:47.576
Four units of packed cells.

714
00:29:47.577 --> 00:29:50.412
two of FFP. 1.000 of TXA...

715
00:29:50.413 --> 00:29:52.873
and 1.200 auto-transfused.

716
00:29:52.874 --> 00:29:55.168
Did you check this?
- Not yet.

717
00:30:03.176 --> 00:30:04.718
Okay. it's working.
Hold compressions.

718
00:30:26.449 --> 00:30:28.075
Okay. we're done.

719
00:30:34.582 --> 00:30:37.835
We stopped at 19:47.

720
00:30:37.836 --> 00:30:38.962
Hey.

721
00:30:41.130 --> 00:30:42.799
Move her to Pedes?

722
00:30:44.801 --> 00:30:46.510
You want me to go with
you to talk to Jake?

723
00:30:46.511 --> 00:30:48.804
No. no. thanks. I got it.

724
00:30:48.805 --> 00:30:52.432
Jesus Christ.

725
00:30:52.433 --> 00:30:53.892
What's going on?

726
00:30:53.893 --> 00:30:55.477
This is bullshit. I
didn't do anything.

727
00:30:55.478 --> 00:30:57.271
He came back to pick up his
mom... they tackled him.

728
00:30:57.272 --> 00:30:58.647
We need to question
him about the shooting.

729
00:30:58.648 --> 00:30:59.815
Okay. After we
clear him medically.

730
00:30:59.816 --> 00:31:01.316
You know the drill.

731
00:31:01.317 --> 00:31:03.068
He has head trauma...
probable concussion.

732
00:31:03.069 --> 00:31:04.486
Dr. Mohan. why don't we do
a complete neurological exam

733
00:31:04.487 --> 00:31:07.156
in BH-2 and put him
in line for a CT?

734
00:31:10.410 --> 00:31:13.328
We got a Pink coming in.

735
00:31:13.329 --> 00:31:14.746
Where's his mom?

736
00:31:14.747 --> 00:31:18.166
Still outside talking
to the police.

737
00:31:18.167 --> 00:31:20.502
This is fucked up. I
didn't do anything.

738
00:31:20.503 --> 00:31:22.337
Then who shot all of
these people. huh?

739
00:31:22.338 --> 00:31:24.673
I don't know. how about you
go look for him. dumbass?

740
00:31:24.674 --> 00:31:26.508
David. are you all right?

741
00:31:26.509 --> 00:31:28.176
No. man. I'm fucking
far from okay.

742
00:31:28.177 --> 00:31:30.178
Okay. okay. we're gonna
get this straightened out

743
00:31:30.179 --> 00:31:32.055
right now.

744
00:31:43.192 --> 00:31:47.195
I'm still bleeding!
Please. I need something.

745
00:31:47.196 --> 00:31:49.531
No hemotympanum. no head trauma.

746
00:31:49.532 --> 00:31:53.785
Pulse is strong at 72.
O2 sat perfect at 99.

747
00:31:53.786 --> 00:31:57.331
Um. do you need pain medicine?

748
00:31:57.332 --> 00:31:58.540
Ma'am. we're trying to help you.

749
00:31:58.541 --> 00:32:01.252
We just need you to let us know.

750
00:32:03.046 --> 00:32:04.838
Okay. let's try and
find her a gurney

751
00:32:04.839 --> 00:32:06.298
and give her a full neuro exam.

752
00:32:06.299 --> 00:32:08.050
Can you put her in 9?

753
00:32:08.051 --> 00:32:10.218
- Drug overdose?
- No.

754
00:32:10.219 --> 00:32:12.220
Normal pupils. normal pulse.

755
00:32:12.221 --> 00:32:14.389
Brain injury?

756
00:32:14.390 --> 00:32:16.016
No. she was walking
with a steady gait.

757
00:32:16.017 --> 00:32:17.392
Still needs a head CT.

758
00:32:17.393 --> 00:32:18.727
Well. that's not
gonna be for hours.

759
00:32:18.728 --> 00:32:21.063
I could drill EZ-IOs
on both sides.

760
00:32:21.064 --> 00:32:23.774
It worked on the last guy.

761
00:32:23.775 --> 00:32:26.401
Maybe it's PTSD
from all she's seen.

762
00:32:26.402 --> 00:32:27.903
Is Psych even here?

763
00:32:27.904 --> 00:32:29.613
No. but maybe she just
needs a quiet place.

764
00:32:29.614 --> 00:32:32.074
Well. knock yourself out.

765
00:32:32.075 --> 00:32:33.784
What's up. Whitaker?

766
00:32:33.785 --> 00:32:35.744
Junctional tourniquet
appears to be working.

767
00:32:35.745 --> 00:32:37.371
No new blood on the gauze.

768
00:32:37.372 --> 00:32:39.290
You're looking good. Carmen.

769
00:32:41.250 --> 00:32:43.710
Is she... Carmen? Carmen?

770
00:32:43.711 --> 00:32:45.587
Pulse is thready. How long
has she been like this?

771
00:32:45.588 --> 00:32:48.590
She was awake and
alert a minute ago.

772
00:32:48.591 --> 00:32:50.384
All that blood loss is
catching up with her.

773
00:32:50.385 --> 00:32:52.095
Run in a liter wide open.

774
00:32:53.930 --> 00:32:56.723
Uh. huge collection of
blood near the bladder.

775
00:32:56.724 --> 00:32:57.766
The bullet must
have tracked north

776
00:32:57.767 --> 00:32:59.101
and hit the external iliac.

777
00:32:59.102 --> 00:33:00.602
We stopped the
bleeding near the leg.

778
00:33:00.603 --> 00:33:02.437
but she's still bleeding
internally... we need Mel.

779
00:33:02.438 --> 00:33:03.772
No. we need to give
a unit of blood

780
00:33:03.773 --> 00:33:05.107
and move her to the red zone.

781
00:33:05.108 --> 00:33:06.609
Okay. let me see
if they have space.

782
00:33:07.610 --> 00:33:09.736
- Coming through.
- Where's Robby?

783
00:33:09.737 --> 00:33:11.279
In BH-2 with the
possible shooter.

784
00:33:11.280 --> 00:33:12.948
Can you guys take a new patient?

785
00:33:12.949 --> 00:33:14.241
Not right now.
What do you got?

786
00:33:14.242 --> 00:33:15.617
Hypotensive pelvic bleed.

787
00:33:15.618 --> 00:33:18.203
Transfuse two units.
We'll get to it.

788
00:33:18.204 --> 00:33:19.621
Abbot!

789
00:33:19.622 --> 00:33:21.415
I got a carotid
injury. popped a clot.

790
00:33:21.416 --> 00:33:22.457
I'll be right there!

791
00:33:22.458 --> 00:33:24.960
Help me out.

792
00:33:24.961 --> 00:33:27.963
- Is that Robby with David?
- Yeah.

793
00:33:27.964 --> 00:33:30.298
I saw the cops bring him in.

794
00:33:30.299 --> 00:33:31.675
Who's David?

795
00:33:31.676 --> 00:33:33.301
High school kid who
was making threats.

796
00:33:33.302 --> 00:33:35.637
- You think he did this?
- Guys. focus on the patients.

797
00:33:35.638 --> 00:33:37.264
What do you got?

798
00:33:37.265 --> 00:33:39.599
Ooh. okay. sterile IV
tubing. umbilical tape.

799
00:33:39.600 --> 00:33:42.686
and red rubber Robinson.
and sterile gloves.

800
00:33:51.821 --> 00:33:53.864
We got a Pink coming in.

801
00:33:53.865 --> 00:33:55.992
Let's take the long way around.

802
00:34:00.913 --> 00:34:02.664
I can put Jake in
the family room.

803
00:34:02.665 --> 00:34:04.332
No. it's okay. I'll do it.

804
00:34:04.333 --> 00:34:05.917
Defect bypass with IV tubing.

805
00:34:05.918 --> 00:34:08.170
You ever done a
Rummel tourniquet?

806
00:34:08.171 --> 00:34:10.298
Robby. can you help
me with a Rummel?

807
00:34:26.773 --> 00:34:28.315
Toughest part is getting
the umbilical tape

808
00:34:28.316 --> 00:34:30.150
through the tubing.

809
00:34:30.151 --> 00:34:32.235
And clamps.

810
00:34:32.236 --> 00:34:34.196
- Very cool.
- You guys got this?

811
00:34:34.197 --> 00:34:35.823
Oh. we're good.

812
00:34:46.292 --> 00:34:48.710
Dr. Robby. I have a
retroperitoneal bleed.

813
00:34:48.711 --> 00:34:50.087
- Get Abbot.
- He's busy.

814
00:34:50.088 --> 00:34:51.922
Okay. stabilize
and find a surgeon.

815
00:34:51.923 --> 00:34:53.424
Get in the chair.

816
00:35:03.601 --> 00:35:05.853
Hey. what's going on?

817
00:35:14.153 --> 00:35:17.739
Leah's injuries
were really serious.

818
00:35:17.740 --> 00:35:19.866
She stopped breathing.

819
00:35:19.867 --> 00:35:23.745
We put a tube down her
throat to deliver oxygen.

820
00:35:23.746 --> 00:35:28.458
We were able to drain the blood
that was collapsing her lungs.

821
00:35:28.459 --> 00:35:31.545
We gave her as much
blood as we could.

822
00:35:31.546 --> 00:35:33.588
We even transfused
some of her own blood

823
00:35:33.589 --> 00:35:35.590
that was in her chest.

824
00:35:35.591 --> 00:35:38.385
But we were unable to...

825
00:35:38.386 --> 00:35:41.472
get ahead of the
massive blood loss.

826
00:35:43.349 --> 00:35:45.101
Her heart stopped.

827
00:35:46.435 --> 00:35:48.479
You saw me doing CPR.

828
00:35:49.939 --> 00:35:52.983
We did
everything that we could.

829
00:35:52.984 --> 00:35:54.694
She's dead?

830
00:36:04.412 --> 00:36:06.079
No. no. but I...
'cause I was talk...

831
00:36:06.080 --> 00:36:07.622
I was talking to her
after she got shot.

832
00:36:07.623 --> 00:36:09.416
and she was talking.

833
00:36:09.417 --> 00:36:12.961
Her heart was damaged
beyond repair.

834
00:36:12.962 --> 00:36:16.631
There was nothing that
we could do to save her.

835
00:36:16.632 --> 00:36:18.800
I want to... I
want to see her.

836
00:36:18.801 --> 00:36:20.302
I'm really sorry.
man. but you can't.

837
00:36:20.303 --> 00:36:22.137
Why not?

838
00:36:22.138 --> 00:36:24.639
Because this is an active
police and FBI investigation.

839
00:36:24.640 --> 00:36:26.641
- She's... she's dead.
- I know.

840
00:36:26.642 --> 00:36:28.393
They're gonna release
her to her parents

841
00:36:28.394 --> 00:36:30.437
in a couple days.

842
00:36:30.438 --> 00:36:32.814
No. please. you... you
have to let me see her.

843
00:36:32.815 --> 00:36:34.734
Please. please. please.

844
00:36:37.278 --> 00:36:38.486
Bringing in mail.

845
00:36:38.487 --> 00:36:40.698
How's she doing?
- Still has a pulse.

846
00:36:44.285 --> 00:36:46.661
What are you doing?
- Prepping for REBOA.

847
00:36:46.662 --> 00:36:48.663
Are you crazy? Did
Abbot approve this?

848
00:36:48.664 --> 00:36:51.666
He said. do what you have to do.

849
00:36:51.667 --> 00:36:53.293
Attendings are all tied up.

850
00:36:53.294 --> 00:36:55.212
If I can blow up a
balloon in the aorta.

851
00:36:55.213 --> 00:36:57.214
it'll stop the bleeding.

852
00:36:57.215 --> 00:36:59.341
It'll cut off the blood
supply to half her body.

853
00:36:59.342 --> 00:37:03.428
I'll only go in a few inches.
zone three. below the kidneys.

854
00:37:03.429 --> 00:37:05.180
until she gets up to the OR.

855
00:37:05.181 --> 00:37:08.016
Glove up. Huckleberry.

856
00:37:08.017 --> 00:37:10.602
Okay. you're gonna need
an ultrasound. X-ray.

857
00:37:10.603 --> 00:37:12.354
Not today.

858
00:37:12.355 --> 00:37:13.855
Have you done this before?

859
00:37:13.856 --> 00:37:15.357
It's a central line.

860
00:37:15.358 --> 00:37:17.442
I just need to hit
the femoral artery...

861
00:37:17.443 --> 00:37:19.361
like that.

862
00:37:19.362 --> 00:37:20.946
Piece of cake.

863
00:37:20.947 --> 00:37:23.531
All right. guidewire.
then introducer sheath.

864
00:37:23.532 --> 00:37:25.033
Santos is doing a REBOA.

865
00:37:25.034 --> 00:37:27.327
- Oh. no. no. no way.
- Yes way.

866
00:37:27.328 --> 00:37:30.288
Um. no. we need an attending
or a senior resident for that.

867
00:37:30.289 --> 00:37:32.583
Oh. ye of little faith.

868
00:37:34.752 --> 00:37:36.796
Victim identification.

869
00:37:40.258 --> 00:37:42.385
Are you sure?
- Yes.

870
00:37:51.894 --> 00:37:55.022
All these people are dead?
- Yeah.

871
00:37:59.986 --> 00:38:02.196
Which one is Leah?

872
00:38:04.323 --> 00:38:07.827
What number do you have
on... on your wrist?

873
00:38:09.578 --> 00:38:11.247
91.

874
00:38:38.190 --> 00:38:40.150
I'm at 15 centimeters

875
00:38:40.151 --> 00:38:43.445
with 5 cc's of saline so far.

876
00:38:43.446 --> 00:38:44.946
A REBOA?

877
00:38:44.947 --> 00:38:46.948
Are you shitting me?
- I told her to stop.

878
00:38:46.949 --> 00:38:48.825
Uncontrollable bleeding
from a pelvic artery...

879
00:38:48.826 --> 00:38:50.410
no other options.

880
00:38:50.411 --> 00:38:51.995
We need an art line to
know if the BP's up.

881
00:38:51.996 --> 00:38:53.955
We'll go with pulse
strength and mentation.

882
00:38:53.956 --> 00:38:56.249
Carotid's weak.
Radial's barely there.

883
00:38:56.250 --> 00:38:57.500
Another 3 cc's in the balloon.

884
00:38:57.501 --> 00:38:58.918
Injecting.

885
00:38:58.919 --> 00:39:00.587
I'll try for palpable systolic.

886
00:39:00.588 --> 00:39:01.714
Yes. go for it.

887
00:39:05.468 --> 00:39:08.053
Whoa. Uh. radial's
much stronger now.

888
00:39:08.054 --> 00:39:09.804
Lock the balloon.
Check the wound.

889
00:39:09.805 --> 00:39:11.139
Go.

890
00:39:11.140 --> 00:39:13.975
- BP's 110 by palp.
- That'll do.

891
00:39:13.976 --> 00:39:15.602
Yeah. wound's dry.
Barely a trickle.

892
00:39:15.603 --> 00:39:17.645
That's because there's no
blood going to her legs.

893
00:39:17.646 --> 00:39:19.105
Okay. the clock is ticking.

894
00:39:19.106 --> 00:39:20.607
Balloon can stay up
for one hour. tops.

895
00:39:20.608 --> 00:39:22.317
Get IR and Vascular on the case.

896
00:39:22.318 --> 00:39:24.652
On it.

897
00:39:24.653 --> 00:39:26.988
Hey. hey. hang in there. Carmen.

898
00:39:26.989 --> 00:39:28.782
You're good.
okay? You're good.

899
00:39:28.783 --> 00:39:31.493
Okay. you never should have
done that on your own. ever.

900
00:39:31.494 --> 00:39:32.870
Do you understand?

901
00:39:34.914 --> 00:39:36.331
But that
was pretty badass.

902
00:39:36.332 --> 00:39:37.833
You saved her life. Good job.

903
00:39:46.384 --> 00:39:49.636
Did you... did you
call her parents?

904
00:39:49.637 --> 00:39:52.013
They'll give the number
to our social worker.

905
00:39:52.014 --> 00:39:54.516
who will contact them very soon.

906
00:39:54.517 --> 00:39:56.351
I got their daughter killed.

907
00:39:56.352 --> 00:39:58.228
This is not your fault.

908
00:40:01.899 --> 00:40:04.234
Why... why couldn't
you save her?

909
00:40:04.235 --> 00:40:06.237
I mean. this...
this is what you do.

910
00:40:10.533 --> 00:40:12.200
I tried.

911
00:40:12.201 --> 00:40:14.786
I
really tried. We all did.

912
00:40:14.787 --> 00:40:16.287
If this had been any
other day. man...

913
00:40:16.288 --> 00:40:17.705
"Had been the other day"?

914
00:40:17.706 --> 00:40:19.124
What the fuck does that
mean. "any other day"?

915
00:40:19.125 --> 00:40:21.043
What. you would've
saved her life?

916
00:40:25.214 --> 00:40:28.049
Yes. No. I don't know.

917
00:40:28.050 --> 00:40:29.969
I don't... I don't know.

918
00:40:31.762 --> 00:40:33.221
We're getting slammed up there.

919
00:40:33.222 --> 00:40:34.848
We've had dozens of
shooting victims.

920
00:40:34.849 --> 00:40:36.349
You've seen it.

921
00:40:36.350 --> 00:40:39.060
The fact that we've saved
as many people as we have

922
00:40:39.061 --> 00:40:41.521
is a fucking miracle.

923
00:40:41.522 --> 00:40:43.690
But you didn't save Leah.

924
00:40:43.691 --> 00:40:44.899
No.

925
00:40:44.900 --> 00:40:46.693
No. I didn't.

926
00:40:48.696 --> 00:40:51.114
And I don't know how many
people I've helped today.

927
00:40:51.115 --> 00:40:53.741
but I can tell you every
other person who has died.

928
00:41:00.082 --> 00:41:01.458
There was a man
named Mr. Spencer.

929
00:41:01.459 --> 00:41:02.959
who died in front
of his children.

930
00:41:02.960 --> 00:41:04.794
and an 18-year-old who...

931
00:41:04.795 --> 00:41:06.921
who was brain dead from
a fentanyl overdose

932
00:41:06.922 --> 00:41:08.715
and a guy with a heart condition

933
00:41:08.716 --> 00:41:11.426
and a little girl who drowned
trying to save her sister.

934
00:41:11.427 --> 00:41:12.719
And I'm
gonna remember Leah

935
00:41:12.720 --> 00:41:14.596
long after you've forgotten her.

936
00:41:14.597 --> 00:41:17.265
Oh. fuck. Oh. fuck.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

937
00:41:17.266 --> 00:41:19.225
You got to go. man.
You... you got to go.

938
00:41:19.226 --> 00:41:21.060
You got to go. You got to go.

939
00:41:21.061 --> 00:41:22.604
Wait. Robby.
Robby. wait. wait.

940
00:41:22.605 --> 00:41:24.522
Put him back in his bed. please.
